## Project-Specific Rules

### Design System — Strictly follow livekit.io visual style
- Background: pure black #000000
- Primary text: white #ffffff
- Secondary text: #a1a1aa (zinc-400)
- Accent / CTA color: green #22c55e
- Border color: #1a1a1a or #27272a (zinc-800)
- Font: Inter from next/font/google
- Border radius: 6px (rounded-md)
- Navbar: fixed, transparent with backdrop-blur, border-bottom #1a1a1a
- Buttons: green background #22c55e with black text for primary CTA, dark outlined for secondary
- Cards: bg #0a0a0a with border #1a1a1a
- No light mode — always dark

### Page Structure — Strictly follow this routing
1. `/` — Landing page that looks exactly like livekit.io homepage
   - Fixed navbar with logo, nav links, "Start building" green CTA button
   - Hero section: large bold headline, subtext, CTA button
   - "Start building" button navigates to `/sign-in`

2. `/sign-in` and `/sign-up` — Auth pages
   - Dark background matching the site theme
   - Google OAuth button
   - Magic link / email login option
   - Minimal centered card layout

3. `/dashboard` — Protected page after login
   - Dark sidebar with only 3 items:
     - Overview
     - Sessions
     - User Settings
   - No pricing, no other pages
   - Dark cards, clean layout

### Component Rules
- Keep all components in `components/` folder with lowercase-dash naming
- Reuse a single `<Navbar />` component across landing and auth pages
- Dashboard uses a `<Sidebar />` component with only the 3 allowed nav items
- No Stripe UI, no billing UI in the dashboard sidebar

### Do not
- Do not add light mode styles
- Do not add extra dashboard pages beyond Overview, Sessions, User Settings
- Do not change the auth logic, only the UI/styling
- Do not remove existing server actions or database queries
